<TITLE> Abul Khair Litu freed on bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 07 (bdnews24.com)  Businessman Abul Khair Litu was freed on bail Wednesday after five months in jail, a senior prisons official said. Major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui, deputy inspector general (prisons), told bdnews24.com that Litu, Bengal Group owner, was freed shortly after 3pm. He had been at Dhaka Medical College Hospital for treatment. "We received the bail order from the High Court Tuesday night," Siddiqui said. Litu arrested on June 3 at his Gulshan home under emergency rules was accused of grabbing land and running businesses that harmed the economy. bdnew
